/wiki\/Jonas_Lie_(writer)\" title=\"Jonas Lie (writer)\">Jonas Lie<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Alexander_Kielland\" title=\"Alexander Kielland\">Alexander Kielland<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Groendahl_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bj%C3%B8rnstjerne_Bj%C3%B8rnson#cite_note-Groendahl-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Bj\u00f8rnson is also celebrated for his lyrics to the Norwegian National Anthem, \"<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ja,_vi_elsker_dette_landet\" title=\"Ja, vi elsker dette landet\">Ja, vi elsker dette landet<\/a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-SNL_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bj%C3%B8rnstjerne_Bj%C3%B8rnson#cite_note-SNL-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Bj\u00f8rnstjerne Bj\u00f8rnson","place_of_birth":"Kvikne ,  Norway","place_of_death":"Paris","text":"Bj\u00f8rnstjerne Bj\u00f8rnson , Literature, 1903","year":1903.0}